                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.79611 Pangborn-Herndon Flight/44:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Forbes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-15T16:00:00+09:00"
                            >August 15, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 15—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>122. I have just been informed that Pangborn and Herndon have been fined 2,050
                    yen each or 205 days in prison. No other penalty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Forbes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
